@binux Sorry I had made this mistake.

When I insert the code below into chrome's console:

```
$('.project-run').on('click', function() {
    var project = $(this).parents('tr').data("name");
    var status = $(this).parents('tr').find(".project-status value").data("value");
    console.log(project);
    console.log(status);
});
```

When you change the status of a project and click run button again it will output the initial state of the project. For example if the initial state of the project is `STOP`, then you change it to `RUNNING`. It will output `STOP` when you click the run button again.

If I change this code to 

```
var status = $(this).parents('tr').find(".project-status [data-value]").attr("data-value");
```

Then it will works properly.

```
def parse_list(self,response):
    for a in response.doc(".href"):
        url = a.attr('href')
        self.detail(url)
        
def detail(url ):
        get_proxy = self.proxy(url )
        if get_proxy:
            self.crawl(url, proxy=get_proxy)
        else:
            self.detail(url )
```

ok, you can change it using a `config.json` file like:

```
{
  "webui": {
    "cdn": "//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/"
  }
}
```

start pyspider with command `pyspider -c config.json`

or just uncomment the code near the line you pointed in app.py.

HG used under runas command 
{{{
runas /savecred /user:vosipov@fastlane.local "hg %*"
}}}
is not worked. No crash, but simple not working. For example, 
{{{
runas /savecred /user:vosipov@fastlane.local "hg init"
}}}
is not create repository.

The problem solved by setting Windows XP compatibility property for hg.exe.


