@ukoethe for reconstructing a broken install:

1. All of your environments are OK.  They all live in $PREFIX/envs (unless you otherwise specify).  You can copy those folders into anywhere else and they should be OK.
2. There is a "recovery mode" in the installer scripts that clobbers the existing install, overwriting whatever the installer contains.  It should make things work again, but leaves the root env in a strange, incomplete metadata state.  Pass the -f flag (for force) to the shell installers.  I'm not sure if a Windows equivalent exists right now.

