I know this is closed, but it really has me stymied. I'm not sure if this should be the intent here as I believe it would introduce thread-safe issues to the library.

At the very least, it makes it very difficult to test schemas. Here's an example (w/3.0.0b12):

```python
from marshmallow import fields, Schema, validates_schema, ValidationError


class ChildSchema(Schema):
    name = fields.Str()

    @validates_schema
    def validate_context(self, data):
        if self.context.get('foo') is not None:
            raise ValidationError('foo is set')

class ParentSchema(Schema):
    child = fields.Nested(ChildSchema())


class TestParentSchema():
    def test_with_context(self):
        schema_with_context = ParentSchema(context={'foo': 'bar'})

        result = schema_with_context.validate({'child': {'name': 'Joe'}})

        assert {'child': {'_schema': ['foo is set']}} == result

    def test_without_context(self):
        schema_without_context = ParentSchema()

        result = schema_without_context.validate({'child': {'name': 'Joe'}})

        assert {} == result
```

In this test run, the second test `test_without_context` will always fail as it is still seeing the context set in the `schema_with_context` variable in the `test_with_context` test.

I suspect the issue is [here](https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/blob/dev/marshmallow/fields.py#L414) but I haven't figured out a way to alter this logic. I've been following the discussion in #302 as well, as it seems to be possibly related to this.

Is there a better way to test schemas with contexts? Happy to open another issue here as well, but it is directly related to this issue so I thought I'd start here.

