One good point that was brought up in #856 by @suquark is that sometimes the number of return values is different for each method invocation. You could imagine allowing the number of return values to vary by doing something like

```python
@ray.remote
class Foo(object):
    def method(self, n):
        return n * (0,)

f = Foo.remote()

id1 = f.method.remote()

id1, id2 = f.method.remote(__ray_num_return_vals__=2)

id1, id2, id3 = f.method.remote(__ray_num_return_vals__=3)
```

